🧪 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
The dataset is analyzed to understand feature distributions, class balance, correlation, and potential data issues before modeling.

🔍 Basic Information
Total Records: 569
Target Classes:
M (Malignant)
B (Benign)
Features: 30 real-valued measurements (e.g., radius, texture, smoothness)

📊 Class Distribution
python
Copy
Edit
df['diagnosis'].value_counts()
Benign: 357
Malignant: 212

📉 Imbalance exists — evaluation metrics like ROC-AUC and Recall are crucial.

