📈 Correlation Heatmap
Features such as radius_mean, area_mean, and perimeter_mean show high correlation with diagnosis.

python
Copy
Edit
sns.heatmap(df.corr(), annot=False, cmap="coolwarm")
📦 Boxplots by Diagnosis
Boxplots of features (e.g., radius_mean, texture_mean) show clear separation between benign and malignant classes, indicating strong predictive potential.

python
Copy
Edit
sns.boxplot(x='diagnosis', y='radius_mean', data=df)
📉 Feature Distributions
Histograms show that some features are skewed and may benefit from standardization.

python
Copy
Edit
df.hist(figsize=(15, 10), bins=30)
✅ Summary of EDA Findings
No missing values or categorical encoding issues
Class imbalance is present (more benign cases)
Some features are highly correlated (good for models like Logistic Regression)
Feature scaling is essential due to varying units and ranges
